A fascinating fact about Vikings is that they were not just fierce warriors but also skilled navigators and explorers. They used a tool called a "sunstone" to help them navigate the seas. This crystal, possibly Icelandic spar, allowed them to determine the position of the sun in overcast or foggy conditions, crucial for their remarkable sea voyages across the North Atlantic and beyond. This technology was way ahead of its time and showcases the Vikings' innovative spirit in exploration. #ancientfacts #coolfacts #vikings #ancienthistory #share #repost #foryoupage #insta

The Chicago River is the only river in the world that flows backward. Originally flowing into Lake Michigan, its course was reversed in 1900 to divert sewage away from the lake, a critical drinking water source for Chicago. This monumental engineering feat used a series of canal locks. #chicagoriver #facts #fyp #insta #reels
